<p>My default implementation with promises looks like:</p>  <pre><code>public F.Promise&lt;Result&gt; index() {    return F.Promise.promise(() -&gt; intensiveComputationSync())        .map(result -&gt; ok(String.valueOf(result))); } </code></pre>  <p>But now I have rx api:</p>  <pre><code>private Observable&lt;Integer&gt; intensiveComputationObservable() {    return Observable.create(subscriber -&gt; {       try {          subscriber.onNext(intensiveComputationSync());       } catch (Exception e) {          subscriber.onError(e);       }       subscriber.onCompleted();    }); } </code></pre>  <p>How I can use my rx api with promises? Especially interested in proper errors handling.</p>